# S01-T03: Piano Integration

## Objective
Copy the provided piano keyboard component into `src/piano/`, remove Next.js directives,
apply the identified `mx-auto` fix, and verify it renders in a smoke-test component.

## Acceptance Criteria
- All 6 files from `incoming/piano-keyboard-export/src/` copied to `src/piano/`.
- Zero `'use client'` directives in any file.
- `PianoKeyboard.tsx` line 117: `max-w-3xl` changed to `max-w-3xl mx-auto`.
- `<PianoKeyboard pressedMidi={null} onChangePressed={() => {}} />` renders in `App.tsx` without errors.
- Console: no TypeScript or runtime errors.

## Steps
1. Copy `components/PianoKey.tsx`, `KeyboardKeybed.tsx`, `PianoKeyboard.tsx` → `src/piano/components/`.
2. Copy `hooks/useNoteFinderKeyboardAudio.ts` → `src/piano/hooks/`.
3. Copy `lib/noteFinderPianoLayout.ts`, `noteFinderKeyboardGeometry.ts`, `noteFinderKeyboardAudioEngine.ts` → `src/piano/lib/`.
4. Remove `'use client';` from all 3 component files.
5. In `PianoKeyboard.tsx`: change `max-w-3xl` to `max-w-3xl mx-auto` (centering fix).
6. Update internal imports to use new paths.
7. Add smoke test render in `App.tsx`, verify in browser.
8. Remove smoke test. `git commit -m "feat: piano keyboard integration + mx-auto fix"`.
